def: Making undue claims and pretension; prone to arrogance. [R.]Dr. H. More.
Carrying pack or burdens on the back; as, a sumpter horse; asumpter mule. Bacon.
Feeding or growing upon decaying anomal or vegetable matter;pertaining to a saprophyte or the saprophytes.
The state of being abstracted; abstract character.
One of the metals, colors, or furs used in armory.
A whitish substance which is cast up, as a scum, from thematerials of glass in fusion, and, floating on the top, is skimmedoff; -- called also glass gall. [Formerly written also sandever.]
Red sulphide of mercury, occurring in brilliant red crystals,and also in red or brown amorphous masses. It is used in medicine.
The quality or state of being spissated; as, the spissitude ofcoagulated blood, or of any coagulum. Arbuthnot.
Bearing something like an open umbrella.
